## Context
Lair run 2026-07-10 (background `make check` on main, doudou): pytest printed
`21 failed, 1388 passed, 32 skipped, 4 errors in 1333s` yet the make process
exited 0. A green gate that cannot fail is no gate. Observation only — cause
not yet established. Candidates: recipe/prerequisite chaining in the Makefile
(`check: check-package | venv-canonicalize`; a later sub-invocation summarised
`25 passed` after the failing suite), or the rtk Bash-hook proxy swallowing the
exit code. Log: `~/.local/share/rtk/tee/1783717128_make_check.log`.

## Actions
1. Reproduce: `make check` on a tree with one deliberately failing fast test;
   record exit codes at each layer (pytest, make, rtk-wrapped shell).
2. Isolate the swallowing layer; fix so failures propagate.

## Test
- A deliberately failing test makes `make check` exit non-zero (mutation-teeth
  check, then revert).

## Exit criteria
- [ ] `make check` exit code equals pytest verdict
- [ ] Mechanism documented in the ticket log
